.TH "debugfs_create_u32_array" 9 "debugfs_create_u32_array" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
debugfs_create_u32_array \- create a debugfs file that is used to read u32 array.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" debugfs_create_u32_array
.BI "(const char *name "  ","
.BI "umode_t mode "  ","
.BI "struct dentry *parent "  ","
.BI "struct debugfs_u32_array *array "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "name" 12
a pointer to a string containing the name of the file to create.
.IP "mode" 12
the permission that the file should have.
.IP "parent" 12
a pointer to the parent dentry for this file.  This should be a
directory dentry if set.  If this parameter is NULL, then the
file will be created in the root of the debugfs filesystem.
.IP "array" 12
wrapper struct containing data pointer and size of the array.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function creates a file in debugfs with the given name that exports
\fIarray\fP as data. If the \fImode\fP variable is so set it can be read from.
Writing is not supported. Seek within the file is also not supported.
Once array is created its size can not be changed.
